    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm trying out NeoVim coming from vim 8 and one very common workflow for me is seemingly missing.\n\nI frequently run commands with `!` like `!make` or `!ls`, etc. In NeoVim it shows the output without toggling the terminal alt buffer, which in a way is nice, since it allows me to see my primary vim window while the command runs, but it also makes the text inaccessible after I press a key to continue.\n\nIn vim I would simple run `!` by itself to toggle the alt buffer and view the output of an old run.\n\nHow is something similar possible in NeoVim?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIdeally my exact workflow would be unchanged, and `!` would show the command buffer with, at the very least, my last command's output.\n\nIf I have to learn a new interface to view each command's output, that's fine though. I just need this to be possible.",
